                                <h4>Insurance in Hong Kong</h4>
                                <p>
                                    There are over 150 authorized insurers in Hong Kong and many of these are general insurers. The Office of the Commissioner of Insurance oversees the insurance industry in Hong Kong. 
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Insurance is the transfer of risk by a person or company to an insurer. The insurer is the company that sells insurance that protects the insured or the policyholder. The money that insurer charges the policyholder for the insurance coverage is called a premium.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    An insurance policy specifies the conditions and circumstances that will determine when the insurer will compensate the insured for any loss.
                                </p>
                                <h4>Useful Tips:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        Before signing an insurance contract, make sure that you understand the policy’s terms, conditions, benefits, and exclusions.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        Disclose all relevant facts, insurance contracts are bound by good faith so material facts must be disclosed.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        Make sure that the policy provides adequate coverage against damage or loss.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        Choose an insurance plan with an affordable premium, missed premium payments can lead to loss of coverage.
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <h4>Insurance Info:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        Insurance is one of the oldest industry in Hong Kong. The goods that were traded between China and Europe in the nineteenth century were already being insured by insurance firms during the nineteenth century.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        Home insurance covers a private residence. It can protect against losses that occurred to one’s home, its contents, or the loss of the homeowner’s personal possessions.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        Medical insurance covers a person’s expenses brought on by sickness or injury. This insures the policyholder from losses from an accident, disability, or accidental death or dismemberment.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        Travel insurance covers the policyholder’s from medical expenses, financial default of travel suppliers, and other losses while traveling either domestically or internationally. Many of these have policies that exclude high risk activities from the coverage like adventure and winter sports.
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
